@FrozenGene Thanks for taking a peek.  I totally understand limited time.

You are right, I do not include a case for Android to skip linking with pthread.  My only excuse was can't really find a solid answer to this in CMake. "if(ANDROID)" would be nice if that's how it is done.  I'll be very happy to implement any suggestion though!
  
I made this "first class" option from the main CMake because a) Its a much better implementation on Windows than the python version, which took a bunch of hacks to make decent performance.  b) Was very easy to link to the tvm libs given its a sub CMake project.
